originalSql:
SELECT 
    COUNT(DISTINCT p.p_partkey) AS distinct_part_count,
    AVG(s.s_acctbal) AS average_supplier_balance,
    STRING_AGG(DISTINCT CONCAT(n.n_name, ': ', s.s_name), ', ') AS supplier_nations
FROM 
    part p
JOIN 
    partsupp ps ON p.p_partkey = ps.ps_partkey
JOIN 
    supplier s ON ps.ps_suppkey = s.s_suppkey
JOIN 
    nation n ON s.s_nationkey = n.n_nationkey
WHERE 
    p.p_retailprice > 50.00
    AND s.s_comment LIKE '%reliable%'
    AND n.n_name IN ('USA', 'Germany', 'Japan')
GROUP BY 
    p.p_name
HAVING 
    COUNT(s.s_suppkey) > 2
ORDER BY 
    average_supplier_balance DESC

SELECT COALESCE("t5"."DISTINCT_PART_COUNT", "t5"."DISTINCT_PART_COUNT") AS "DISTINCT_PART_COUNT", "t5"."AVERAGE_SUPPLIER_BALANCE", "t5"."SUPPLIER_NATIONS"
FROM (SELECT "t1"."p_name", COUNT(DISTINCT "t1"."p_partkey") AS "DISTINCT_PART_COUNT", AVG("t0"."s_acctbal") AS "AVERAGE_SUPPLIER_BALANCE", LISTAGG(DISTINCT CONCAT("t"."n_name", ': ', "t0"."s_name"), ', ') AS "SUPPLIER_NATIONS", COUNT(*) AS "FD_D_f4"
FROM (SELECT *
FROM "nation"
WHERE "n_name" IN ('Germany', 'Japan', 'USA')) AS "t"
INNER JOIN (SELECT *
FROM "supplier"
WHERE "s_comment" LIKE '%reliable%') AS "t0" ON "t"."n_nationkey" = "t0"."s_nationkey"
INNER JOIN ((SELECT *
FROM "part"
WHERE "p_retailprice" > 50.00) AS "t1" INNER JOIN "partsupp" ON "t1"."p_partkey" = "partsupp"."ps_partkey") ON "t0"."s_suppkey" = "partsupp"."ps_suppkey"

ORDER BY 3 DESC NULLS FIRST) AS "t5"
